
[1]fallacious

   FALLA'CIOUS, a. [L. fallax, from fallo, to deceive. See Fail.]

   1. Deceptive; deceiving; deceitful; wearing a false appearance;
   misleading; producing error or mistake; sophistical; applied to things
   only; as a fallacious argument or proposition; a fallacious appearance.

   2. Deceitful; false; not well founded; producing disappointment;
   mocking expectation; as a fallacious hope.
